Title: Stochastic Processes and the Dirac Equation with External Fields

Authors: Jae-weon Lee, Eok Kyun Lee, Hae Myoung Kwon, In-gyu Koh, Yeong Deok

HanComments: 9 pages, 1 figure, scalar parts eliminated

Journal-ref: J.Korean Phys.Soc. 41 (2002) 164-166

The equation describing the stochastic motion of a classical particle in1+1-dimensional space-time is connected to the Dirac equation with externalgauge fields. The effects of assigning different turning probabilities to theforward and the backward moving particles in time are discussed.